application_type_full: Outline planning permission: Some matters reserved
description: Redevelopment of the site for mixed-use purposes, including the alteration and conversion of the Millennium Mills and the construction of buildings for residential, shop, food and drink, leisure (including an aquarium), office, hotel, community and education uses; provision of public open space; works of repair and restoration of the dock walls including temporary use of water areas for working space; infilling and excavation of parts of the dock area; and the use of the dock area for the mooring of barges; the placing of structures in, on or over the dock area; the construction of a pedestrian bridge across the North Woolwich Road from the site to the DLR station; construction of a vehicular and pedestrian bridge to link the east and west of the site; construction of estate roads and the creation of new accesses to the public highway; works of landscaping and making good; creation of surface and sub-surface car parking areas.
